

**The Obsidian Lanterns — Complete Linear Chronicle, Chapters 1–21**

The story begins in Riften. The party of six takes a job from Maven Black-Briar to clear Thornheart Grove, a shifting maze overrun with plant corruption. They fight treants, spriggans with woodcutter faces grown into them, and the Heart-Keeper boss. Danica the priestess is freed. The High Elf Falsetto joins briefly. They return to Riften, get paid, and travel to Whiterun where Jarl Balgruuf summons them to solve the Lars Battleborn murder — Idolaf confesses. They are then summoned to Falkreath.

In Falkreath they meet the old Khajiit Ja'ha, and the mercenary character Alfonso (Nick's PC) is officially integrated. The corrupt Dunmer Alfonso eats from a grave. Nenya the steward hires them to investigate four disappearances. They work the lumber mill, gather clues, discover the Hall of the Honored Dead, and open it with the passphrase "Valerius Caelus." Inside: a vampire cult. A nightshade miasma chamber. Four caged prisoners. They descend through the dungeon fighting a Dark Elf vampire, a death hound, and two stronger vampires — a High Elf and a Nord who bites and kills Ja'ha mid-fight, turning her into a Stage 1 vampire. Seraleth the furious High Elf who had been lost inside also gets infected. An Argonian Blood-Knight vampire drops from the library ceiling. They fight in the library — an epic battle. Seraleth is killed by a pouncing fledgling and comes back infected.

Chapter 7 brings the Preservatory — a sterile alchemical chamber with four prisoners being drained into crystal reservoirs. Davinia yanks out the tubes on Kust, causing damaging feedback. Orion figures out to freeze the reservoirs first. Danica and Davinia share a romantic moment firing sunbeam and ash shell together holding hands. They read Valerius's diary and enter his crypt. Valerius dominates Kyboh's will and Kyboh uses his ultimate attack on Davinia, sending her into the wall.

The Wager: Alfonso negotiates with Valerius mid-combat and agrees to be turned as a deal to let everyone leave. Orion volunteers too. Ja'ha and Alfonso feed on Orion. Danica is terrified; Davinia kisses her and promises eternal protection. Valerius lets them all go. They lie to Nenya, get paid 800 gold each, and a morning courier arrives: High King Torygg summons them to Solitude. On the road Alfonso fireballs Imperial tax collectors, killing six. They pass Dragon Bridge inspection with their cloaks and arrive in Solitude. Legate Quintus escorts them to the Winking Skeever.

In Solitude: Ja'ha leaves at night for Morthal to find Valerius permanently. Alfonso seduces and entirely consumes a Dunmer shopkeeper. Orion kills a homeless man. Davinia and Danica go to the docks on a date; the Crown saves a fisherman from a dock fire. Kyboh finds an ancient snowflake shield at the market. Orion enrolls in the Bards College and improves his war horn. Saijah connects to Skyrim's plant network at the Temple of Divines through a dying Gildergreen sapling and senses Mythic Dawn cult corruption in Solitude. Davinia meets General Tullius — her parents are coming. The party goes to the Blue Palace, where Krusp Fanck "the Ashen Blade" is introduced. Court intrigue: Thane Erikur tries to manipulate Kyboh, Lady Bryling informs Saijah of political stakes, Jarl Elisif reveals worry about Torygg's safety. The party intervenes in the courtyard to protect a boy from Thalmor arrest for Talos worship. Torygg charters them as Skyrim's Wardens, grants the Royal Charter, pays 1,200 gold each. Orion does his Dark Brotherhood audition in the Hall of the Dead — kills a mage silently, dismembers the body as art, joins the Brotherhood, receives shrouded armor.

Chapter 10: Last-minute shopping, then they travel with Krusp. On the road Krusp lectures on dragons. They hear Alduin's roar and rush to Kynesgrove. Stormcloaks arrive with news — Ulfric killed Torygg. The charter now operates under a dead king. The village is in ruins. The party splits: boys handle cultists (Krusp kills one who murders a hostage; Alfonso does "sexual interrogation"; Orion bites the last cultist from the groin; Alfonso consumes the body; Krusp covers for them with survivors). The girls save all 16 inn survivors in five minutes — Davinia uses the ice crown, Danica refuses to leave. Alduin appears and resurrects Sahloknir.

The Sahloknir fight. The impossible punch: Kyboh's Doubling enchantment flares back delivering mountain-breaking damage to the dragon — exit wound visible on the other side, gloves shatter, Kyboh is in agony, the dragon flees in fear. Saijah shoots the wing joint, the dragon crashes. Kyboh delivers the killing blow. The dragon's soul disappears — which shouldn't happen. They loot the hoard. Bjorn clutches his chest. Alfonso accidentally creates a plague ghoul from a dying man. Davinia and Danica share their first real night together. Campfire confrontation: Krusp condemns the party — he saw Alfonso eat the cultist, knows Falkreath was a failed negotiation, not a victory. He warns Danica to flee, swears to hunt Alfonso and Orion if they prey on innocents, takes 500 gold and walks away east toward Windhelm.

Korvanjund part 1: The aftermath. Ulfric killed Torygg by Thu'um. Alfonso eats a sick horse. Bjorn gives them three urgent choices; they choose Korvanjund. Ylva "the Cleaver" blocks their path, challenges them, joins. She beats Alfonso unconscious twice sparring. Bandit encounter — Davinia lets one go with 20 gold. Galmar Stone-Fist is Davinia's "Uncle Galmar." They flank Dragon Cult battlemages via a cliff path and eliminate them. Inside: falling platform trap, descend fighting. They repair two mechanisms. Davinia and Danica kiss properly for the first time. Alfonso asks Ylva for a kiss; she says sure. Alfonso has 16 plague ghouls from the bone pits. Most Stormcloaks die. Ulag the Breaker — ancient Orcish war machine — gives his monologue and the battle begins.

Korvanjund part 2: Ulag crits Davinia, Kyboh, and Orion down immediately. Saijah fires from invisibility and nearly kills Ulag. Ulag collapses the tomb and escapes. Desperate escape with the 20,000 gold chest. All escape. Galmar promotes Hroki to Captain. Galmar gives Davinia his house seal. Then a blood-letter from Valerius arrives — dried blood, claiming Davinia as "cousin" of the Caelinus branch, threatening to expose the tax collector murders unless she comes to discuss a dynasty.

Chapter 14, The Winter Road: Father's letter arrives demanding she come to Castle Dour. Three competing father-figures. Alfonso's plague ghoul explodes into four pieces. Kyboh's fingers are calcifying. Refugees appear with Dagonic wood-corruption — bark growing from skin. Davinia passes them by under the Crown's influence. Varon pressures Orion about his contract timeline. Ylva and Davinia have a campfire moment. They arrive at Winterhold, welcomed as heroes. At the College, Faralda lets them in after tests. Davinia discovers her fire magic has been permanently replaced by Atmoran black ice — the Crown did it without asking. Something pulses in the Midden. Ancano is watching.

Chapter 15, The City of Sparks: Kyboh trades the snowflake shield to Urag for research on Hjolmar Ice-Shaper. Alfonso meets Sergius at the Soul's Anvil and is sent to the Midden for Void Salts. Ancano intercepts Davinia — give him the Focal Crystal or he'll destroy her father's career. The party enters the Midden. The Crown's black ice destroys Focal Flame Atronachs. Ice writing on the walls — Davinia touches it and the Crown gives her Wizard Sight. The Tonal Flesh Atronach triggers a catastrophic detonation killing everyone. Saijah sacrifices her Hawk's Talon and Hawk's Feather to Kynareth. Kynareth answers and heals everyone. They beat the Atronach with magic only. The Void Atronachs — Crown takes Davinia's memory of her mother's warmth in exchange for knowledge. The Atronach Forge fight. The Crown replaces Davinia's right hand with Ismara's ice architecture construct. In the Augur's chamber Kyboh accidentally removes the Focal Crystal. A Black Root at the deepest point — Dagon cultist trapped in crystal inside an Eldergleam root that tunneled underground from Eastmarch. Nora asks to join; Alfonso says yes. The Singing Sea crossing with seven major obstacles. Hjolmar's glacier reached. The door opens with the three snowflake items: shattered gloves, Boots of the Comet, Alfonso's Jagged Crown — now the Crown of Namira, Alfonso having traded his permanent sense of satiation. Hjolmar diagnoses Kyboh: the glove enchantment is in his bones — the Titan's Tithe is in his marrow. He gives Kyboh the Anchor of Stasis. Ismara is building her laboratory inside Davinia's head, replacing her piece by piece. Alfonso's "two songs" diagnosis: months not years. Hjolmar assigns them to retrieve the Aetherial Matrix from Mzinchaleft.

Chapter 16, The Deep Archive: Two days southwest to Mzinchaleft. Alfonso's beetles organize on his hand as Namira and Peryite try to harmonize. Saijah feels the dying root network across the Pale. Three spider sentinels ambush them — Kyboh's Anchor makes him immune to their enchantment attacks. The Glitching Sphere: Orion uses the Diagnostic Song deliberately for the first time to walk past undetected. They descend into Mzinchaleft — an intact city, everyone vanished simultaneously. Personal moments in the dead city: Kyboh finds a brass horse figurine, Orion discovers resonance chambers, Alfonso's plague is neutralized by the city's air, Saijah's migraine goes completely quiet. They descend to Blackreach. The Cognitorium sphere. GEAR is activated — the Cognitorium Attendant, running for 4,287 years, polite and curious. The Matrix is with the Primary Centurion two tiers below. Nora has a profound reaction to GEAR. Saijah and Orion give GEAR permission to leave the Cognitorium. GEAR crosses the threshold for the first time in his existence. Saijah hugs him.

Chapter 17, The Heart of Brass: The Optical Translation Array — 2,300 Snow Elf refugees used as living Elder Scroll processors, average lifespan 14 months after processing. The party's horror. Ismara whispers "Efficient." Alfonso walks out without a word — the first time in the campaign he looks disturbed. They return for the engineering key. Davinia drapes a Dwemer tunic on GEAR; he's delighted, but his own gears shred it. GEAR's response: "I will maintain it carefully." Outside the Centurion room: 30 minutes of strategy debate. GEAR points out Orion won't be detected by Detect Life. Orion and GEAR approach — GEAR enthusiastically announces "Friend Orion! I have the payload!" waking the Centurion. The fight: Alfonso ages the marble floor for noise traps, Saijah throws the key across the room and it lands perfectly in the chest keyhole, Davinia uses the Wizard Hand to turn it via telekinesis. Nora faints. Varon extracts the Matrix silently and effortlessly — his defining moment of competence. Varon tries to smile at Saijah and gets distracted. Ylva finally gets the green light, charges laughing, gets hit hard, spits blood, smiles. Saijah fires the perfect shot through the chest cavity through every internal gear to the single central powerline. The Centurion dies. A spider worker tries to fix it for 30 seconds, gives up, retreats. GEAR: "I will log a maintenance request. Though I suppose no one is coming to fulfil it. Are they." Kyboh removes the Anchor of Stasis during the fight and barely notices.

Chapter 18, The Long Road Home: Kyboh reaches for the Matrix without the Anchor — his bone enchantment synchronizes with it tonally, the resonance builds, amber light crawls up his body converting flesh into sound. Things fall from him: the focusing crystal, potions, his dragonbone greatsword splitting into four pieces. He looks confused, not afraid. Then a point of light contracts and shoots upward through a mile of stone and vanishes. The Cognitorium alarm triggers — biological purge, all lights turn crimson. GEAR: 4.2% survival probability. The desperate escape: fighting up the spiral staircase against Dwemer Spheres, Nora shot by a crossbow bolt and nearly falls — Davinia catches her with the Wizard Hand. The lift shaft ascent through maintenance spiders. Orion plays a frequency tuned to spider neural pathways and freezes them all for three seconds — giving everyone time to breathe. They reach the city level: 11,000 Spider Workers in biological purge mode, flooding the corridor. Alfonso reaches past his reserves into his life force and uses both divine songs simultaneously — the beam fills the corridor wall to wall and unmakes three full rooms of spiders. He drops to one hit point. Davinia drags him. Ylva is stabbed through the shoulder by a spider's manipulator arm and dies — then Hircine refuses to let her stay dead. She transforms into a werewolf for the first time. Nine feet of rage and muscle tears through the swarm covering the party's retreat. The final lift: Saijah air-dashes to the maintenance gantry and fires down to redirect the flood while the others hit the four tube notes. The platform launches upward. At the surface Ylva stumbles out naked, human again, and collapses in the snow.

Outside: Davinia falls to her knees and dents the bronze doors with the Wizard Hand. Alfonso walks away. Saijah cries silently. Orion stands in disbelief. Bjorn immediately asks where Kyboh is. Ylva grabs Alfonso and takes him behind bushes for sex, then transforms back naked. Saijah offers a cloak; Ylva drapes it without covering anything. Nora asks Alfonso to teach her how to use life energy instead of FP; he does. Saijah prays to Kynareth and gets the same non-specific answer — frustrated. Varon flirts badly with Saijah and then a courier brings Orion the Dark Brotherhood contract for Grelod the Kind. Bjorn passes around cups for everyone including an empty sixth cup for Kyboh, and speaks about him — how Kyboh reminded him of himself when young. GEAR, after being told what the sixth cup is for, says "I believe I was pouring the sixth cup" — he has been maintaining systems for 4,287 years for researchers who will never return. Orion and Ylva hunt together; Orion freezes a hunter and drinks him like a slushy, ruining it for Ylva who abandons him. In the dark Alfonso makes his phylactery — pours his soul into the iron dagger, transforming it into a corroded rapier, making himself a lich of Peryite. His body can no longer be physically damaged but his iron rapier can rust and corrode. Davinia sees it through Wizard Sight: his body is dark, no aura, no soul. They break camp in the morning. Then Krosulhah attacks.

Chapter 19, The Blood Price: Krosulhah dives — Blood-Fire breath, scorched road, Nora and Davinia combine ash shell and ice to protect the cart and Mable. Orion's Diagnostic Song reads the dragon: 560 HP across two phase bars, DR 12, Slipstream in air making projectiles nearly useless. Orion's Movement of Entropy grinds down the DR. Alfonso fires sustained lightning ignoring the slipstream. Saijah air-dashes to a ledge. Davinia spots a fractured overhang and tears it down with the Wizard Hand — thousands of tons of rock strike Krosulhah mid-flight, crumpling his wing. He crashes. Now grounded, he's worse — his tail demolishes the cliff walls, his Wing Buffet scatters the party, DR back to full. Alfonso channels through the corrupted rapier for three turns, building a focused beam of lightning that punches through the scales. The rapier darkens further. Nora charges four turns and converts fire to frost via somatic swap, flash-freezing the damaged wing and shattering it. Varon climbs the dragon's back and stabs at the gaps between scales. Saijah puts an arrow through Krosulhah's left eye. Davinia throws GEAR into the ruined eye socket. GEAR clamps onto the optic nerve and fires Tonal Pulses directly into the dragon's brain, disrupting its nervous system. Saijah fires her last enchanted arrow — chain lightning — aimed at GEAR. The lightning discharges through the brass into the optic nerve through the dragon's spinal column to the heart. Krosulhah's body seizes and falls. The dragon's soul erupts — not upward but down the road toward where Bjorn is with the horses. It vanishes behind the cliff wall.

When they round the bend, Bjorn is against the wall. He looks different — younger, straighter, his stiff hands now fluid and strong. Davinia through Wizard Sight sees two dragon souls burning inside him. Orion looks at Bjorn, at the dragonbone shard Bjorn carries, and says to nobody in particular: "What if Bjorn is the Dragonborn?"

After the fight: The Crown offers Davinia a trade — capture the dragon's Blood-Fire frequency in a sphere of ice architecture in exchange for her autonomic breath. She accepts. Every breath now requires a conscious fraction of effort. Saijah sees the change and crosses to her; holds her fiercely. Where the Crown touches Saijah's hair, the color bleeds to white from the point of contact. Neither notices. Then Saijah finds her Hawk's Talon and Hawk's Feather lying on the scorched road — returned. Nora trains further with both Alfonso (sword-as-focus, directed beam) and Orion (tonal engineering). Ylva tries to connect with Saijah; it goes awkwardly stilted until Saijah simply refuses to engage with Ylva's territorial dynamic — "Chill out. You're being too much." Hircine appears as a white stag and speaks to Saijah — he's impressed she hunted a dragon, offers her a bargain: hunt another dragon, bring him the kill, and he'll give her the power to save the Eldergleam. Saijah says no — with a hesitation Hircine hears and files away. The cart moves south. In the Rift, Saijah's migraine returns as the dying root network reconnects. Alfonso stares at the rust spreading on his rapier — the next time he channels hard through it, it will spread further, and eventually the tarnish will reach him. Bjorn grows stronger every day, quieter every day, terrified of what he's becoming. Varon asks Davinia how to talk to Saijah like a person. Davinia has nothing to give. They arrive at Riften — city is fine, gates open, no catastrophe. At the gate: Maven Black-Briar's official notice crediting the Obsidian Lanterns and "their priestess DANICA PURE-SPRING" for saving the city and curing Hemming. The greatest heroic act the Lanterns ever performed happened entirely because they were somewhere else.

Chapter 20, The City That Didn't Need You: Bjorn stops them before the gates for disguise — hood down for Davinia, Ataxia story for Alfonso, actual pants for Ylva. They enter Riften. The memorial stone with the plague victims' names. The notice on the wall. In the market, Krusp stops Davinia: "She doesn't know you're here. Give her the choice. Don't ambush her with this." He's become Danica's friend. Davinia goes to the Temple of Mara. Danica is there, visibly aged and carrying new calm authority. She asks immediately: "Where's Kyboh?" Then she leads Davinia upstairs to the wedding hall. The six points: Danica delivers her prepared speech — measured, clear, devastating. You held my face and slapped my hands away. You sent me into the wilderness alone. You compared yourself to your father and then did the same thing to me. Kyboh signed the note and was the only one who made her feel wanted. You decide things for people and call it love — it's control. She's leaving not because she hates Davinia but because she is a better healer, priestess, and person when not waiting for Davinia to decide what's best for her. The door stays cracked — not open, not shut — the width of a paw print. Davinia doubles down on the Crown being necessary rather than saying "I was wrong." Danica says: when you can say I was wrong without telling me why you were right, come find me.

Alfonso finds Danica on the steps and tells her he thinks leaving is a mistake — "because being needed is worth more than being right." Danica presses her face against his chest and cries; first time the group's serial killer has offered comfort and meant it. Davinia goes back to find Krusp praying and asks him to deliver an amulet of Mara to Danica. He refuses: "Deliver it yourself. Or don't. But I am not your courier." The Crown goes silent — Ismara, for once, has nothing to add because Krusp has just made the case for integration better than she ever could.

Hircine's gift activates without asking in Riften's lower city — Saijah's pupils dilate, she can hear heartbeats through walls, smell blood two streets over. Ylva confronts her about it territorially. Saijah: "Chill out. You're being too much." Maven summons them to the Bee and Barb — Danica already collected their Thornheart Grove reward: 10,000 gold, Maven's personal favour, and the Aegis. Maven has a new problem: someone poisoned her Meadery. Five thousand gold for intelligence on who did it. They accept.

They spend a day at Balimund's forge — 7,000 gold in repairs and new gear. Davinia orders a symbol of Mara engraved on her ebony mace. It glows faintly when Balimund returns it. A street urchin bumps into Davinia and leaves a dead drop in her pocket: a heavy iron key wrapped in stained parchment. The note: "The Golden Eagles took my shield in Riverwood and are now in the sewers looking for me. The World-Eater wakes. I know how to kill the black god. The Warrens, bottom level. Use the key. Hurry."

Into the Ratway: ten gold per head to Dirge at the fork. The Flagon — underground cistern tavern. Brynjolf confirms: four Thalmor in the lower Vaults hunting an old scholar who's been paying rent in decades-old coins. The scholar is Esbern. He's been there thirty years. Orion separately gathers intelligence on Honorhall Orphanage and Grelod. Deeper into the Warrens — a shantytown in abandoned sewer infrastructure. Fresh damage: a door kicked off its hinges. A body — travel-worn leathers, courier's satchel, throat cut with surgical precision. The courier Caius Varro of the Blades, killed ten feet from delivering his letter.

Two items change everything: The Blades letter describing Sky Haven Temple in the Karthspire — Alduin's Wall, a complete prophecy, a Shout to force a dragon from the sky, and a carved depiction of a council of heroes who are not Dragonborn — the Akaviri prepared for the Dragonborn failing. The Thalmor dispatch case: the Thalmor are deliberately allowing the Dagon cult to corrupt the Eldergleam because it serves their strategic objectives. The Tower Protocol — the Thalmor's true objective is not conquest but the dissolution of the metaphysical anchors holding the mortal plane together. The end of physical existence for every being bound to it. And a tracking list: every Obsidian Lantern is on it. The Khajiit listed as neutralized. Esbern: extract team deployed.

Orion feeds in the Warrens — the Argonian woman, left pinned to a wall by an ice spike. Alfonso infects a skooma addict with his plague — the Warrens will spread it without knowing. Then: Mila. Eight years old, fetching water for her sick mother. Saijah hears the child's heartbeat through the wall with Hircine's gift. They find the mother — dying of Forelhost Strain 1.0, Antoine's engineered pathogen from the Black-Briar Meadery. Alfonso infects her with his own strain, which consumes Antoine's plague. The mother is cured and becomes an asymptomatic carrier of Alfonso's disease. He also reads from the transmission the identity of the architect: Antoine of Forelhost. The negotiation with the mother: 100 gold. She doesn't hesitate. Mila is sold. Saijah leads the child through the tunnels, the child's hand locked around her wrist, learning that forward is the only direction left.

They descend to the Vaults. Two booms — a Thalmor kill squad breaking through Esbern's door. Saijah's bow is up before she decides to raise it. One shot: the arrow catches the staff at its crystal focus and the contained lightning detonates in a sphere. All four Thalmor die. Darkness. Esbern is alive behind the door. They open it — 30 years of maps and books and obsessive preparation. Esbern asks about Caius, reads the answer in their faces before they speak. He asks for the Dragonstone from Bleak Falls Barrow — without it they fight blind, waiting for dragons to find them rather than the reverse. He packs three irreplaceable books and joins them.

On the surface: Bjorn sees Mila. The brush slips from his hand. Everything he is changes in an instant — the weathered exasperation replaced by something chilling and still. He moves with liquid, unhurried precision that belongs to someone younger and vastly more dangerous. "Whose child is that." When told what happened, the dam breaks — he condemns them for dragging a child into the apocalypse. He drops to one knee in front of Mila: "What's your name, little one?" He leads her to the cart and points out the loose nail. Then turns back to the party and says to take her to Honorhall. Orion reveals what Honorhall actually is. Bjorn's working model of the world breaks. He recognizes the shape — a fine estate, a door arrived at too late, two hours too long. "There is nowhere to leave her." She stays on the cart with him. He looks at Orion and files something under a heading without speaking it. "If you let the darkness you carry spill over and catch her in the crossfire — I will pack the cart, take her, and leave. And I won't ever come back."

Three fire-couriers over the following days: A young Stormcloak soldier dying of Alfonso's plague — the medical supplies seeded at Korvanjund killed half of Galmar's First Cohort on the march to Dawnstar. Vokun watched from Dawnstar's walls as the Stormcloak army dismantled itself. Galmar begs for help. Davinia says "We'll come" — the only thing to say; it doesn't make it clean. Then Klimmek bursts through the door: the 7,000 Steps are bleeding black sap, men in grey robes with faces of horn and fire, the air felt like time was wrong. He ran all the way from the mountain. The Dagon cult is on the most sacred path in Skyrim, between the world and the sky.

Three directions. Three crises. Bjorn puts a cigar in his teeth and drinks. Davinia finds him at the bar. He tells her his full backstory — the War-Hound, the two sisters Lylana and Anya, the noble's hunting party, running for hours and arriving two hours too late, killing everyone in the estate with his hands and staying until morning. He buried who he was. Became Bjorn. He confirms he knows Davinia has seen something when she looks at him with Wizard Sight, and that it doesn't need to be said aloud. He says Kyboh reminded him of himself before he learned what fast was for. And then: "We're going to get him back." Not a question. Davinia says it back.

They sit together in the Bee and Barb, in a city that saved itself without them, and understand each other perfectly. Outside, Mila presses a loose nail on the cart with one finger, learning what morning looks like when it comes through open sky.

---

